curam.util.common.domain

Interface Domains


  • public interface Domains
    An interface to a collection of domains providing access to domains in the domain hierarchy by name and supporting the addition of new domains. Once a domain has been retrieved, the domain hierarchy can be traversed via that domain's API.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      Domain getDomain(java.lang.String name)
      Gets a domain given its name.

    • Method Detail

      • getDomain

        Domain getDomain(java.lang.String name)
          throws DomainException
        Gets a domain given its name. It is a critical error if the domain name cannot be resolved, as this indicates a bug in the generation of code or the processing of data.
        Parameters:
        name - The name of the domain.
        Returns:
        The named domain.
        Throws:
        DomainException - If the domain name cannot be resolved.
